.\" docs/man/meow.1
.TH MEOW 1 "2025-08-08" "meowg1k" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
meow \- your purr-sonal AI sidekick for the terminal
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B meow
[\fIcommand\fR] [\fIflags\fR] [\fIarguments...\fR]
.br
For command\-specific flags, run:
.B meow
\fIcommand\fR \-\-help
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B meow
is a fast, script\-friendly AI CLI. It talks to cloud models
(Gemini 2.5: Pro & Flash) and local inference (llama.cpp), supports reusable
tasks, and uses layered configuration for reproducible workflows.
.br
Input can be provided via flags and/or piped through stdin.

.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B generate
Generate any content based on input \- code, text, or docs. Works with Gemini or llama.cpp.
.TP
.B version
Show version info.
.TP
.B completion
Generate shell completion scripts.

.SH OPTIONS
Global options:
.TP
.BR \-h , " \-\-help"
Show help for
.B meow
or a specific command.

.SH PROVIDERS
.TP
.B gemini  (default)
Google Gemini 2.5 (Pro/Flash). Requires
.B MEOW_GEMINI_API_KEY
in environment.
.TP
.B llama
Local
.BR llama.cpp
HTTP server. The model is chosen by the server; use
.B \-\-llama\-base\-url
to connect.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B MEOW_GEMINI_API_KEY
API key for the Gemini provider.

.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration files are read with the following precedence:
.IP "1." 3
Project config:
.B ./.meowg1k/config.yaml
.IP "2."
User config:
.B ~/.config/meowg1k/config.yaml
.PP
Flags always override configuration values.

.SH EXAMPLES
Explain Go code with Gemini Pro:
.br
.B cat main.go | meow g \-m gemini\-2.5\-pro \-p "Explain this code"
.PP
Refactor with Gemini Flash:
.br
.B cat component.js | meow g \-m gemini\-2.5\-flash \-p "Refactor for performance"
.PP
Use a strict system prompt:
.br
.B cat utils.go | meow g \-m gemini\-2.5\-pro \-s "You are a senior Go engineer focusing on concurrency and safety" \-p "Review this for race conditions"
.PP
Local llama.cpp server (model chosen by server):
.br
.B meow g \-P llama \-u http://127.0.0.1:8080 \-p "Summarize this code"
.PP
Run a reusable task from config:
.br
.B cat app.py | meow g \-t pytest\-gemini

.SH FILES
.B ~/.config/meowg1k/config.yaml
\- user configuration
.br
.B ./.meowg1k/config.yaml
\- project configuration

.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 on success, non\-zero on error.

